      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Programming\" title=\"Programming\">Programming</a> * <a href=\"/Languages\" title=\"Languages\">Languages</a> * Delphi</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Collier-priestess_of_Delphi.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Collier-priestess_of_Delphi.jpg/330px-Collier-priestess_of_Delphi.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"606\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Collier-priestess_of_Delphi.jpg/500px-Collier-priestess_of_Delphi.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/Collier-priestess_of_Delphi.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Collier-priestess_of_Delphi.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/Category:John_Collier\" title=\"Category:John Collier\">John Collier</a> - Priestess of Delphi <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Delphi</b>,<br />\na programming language dialect of the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object_Pascal\">Object Pascal</a> programming language, a branch of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object-oriented_programming\">object-oriented</a> derivatives of <a href=\"/Pascal\" title=\"Pascal\">Pascal</a>, mostly known as the primary programming language of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embarcadero_Delphi\">Embarcadero Delphi</a>, formerly CodeGear Delphi, Inprise Delphi and Borland Delphi , designed and implemented by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anders_Hejlsberg\">Anders Hejlsberg</a>, the creator of <a href=\"/Pascal#TurboPascal\" title=\"Pascal\">Turbo Pascal</a>. As a chief architect at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borland\">Borland</a> , Hejlsberg secretly turned Turbo Pascal into an object-oriented application development language, complete with a truly visual environment and superb database-access features. Developer <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Danny_Thorpe\">Danny Thorpe</a> chose the name <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delphi\">Delphi</a>, in reference to the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pythia\">Oracle at Delphi</a>.\n</p><p>Delphi provides an <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integrated_development_environment\">Integrated development environment</a> for <a href=\"/Microsoft\" title=\"Microsoft\">Microsoft</a> <a href=\"/Windows\" title=\"Windows\">Windows</a> applications. Delphi pioneered in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rapid_application_development\">rapid application development</a> by introducing an <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Application_framework\">application framework</a> and visual window layout designer that drastically reduced application prototyping times of <a href=\"/GUI\" title=\"GUI\">GUI</a> and Database applications. Delphi XE <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> is now part of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embarcadero_Technologies\">Embarcadero</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embarcadero_Delphi#RAD_Studio\">RAD Studio</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, including <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2BBuilder\">C++Builder</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unified_Modeling_Language\">UML</a> modeling <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, still supporting <a href=\"/X86\" title=\"X86\">x86</a> <a href=\"/Assembly#InlineAssembly\" title=\"Assembly\">inline assembly</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. A former <a href=\"/Linux\" title=\"Linux\">Linux</a> version of Borland Delphi, called <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kylix_%28software%29\">Kylix</a> discontinued.  In 2009, Embarcadero announced 64-bit, Linux and <a href=\"/Mac_OS\" title=\"Mac OS\">Mac OS</a> support <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> . \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Software\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Software</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Misc\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Misc</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Delphi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Generic_Programming\" title=\"Generic Programming\">Generic Programming</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Pascal\" title=\"Pascal\">Pascal</a></li>\n<li> <span id=\"DelphiEngines\"></span><a href=\"/Category:Delphi\" title=\"Category:Delphi\">Engines written in Delphi</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Delphi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://comp.lang.pascal.delphi.misc.narkive.com/HW7VUOEV/martin-harvey-thread-tutorial\">Martin Harvey</a> (<b>2000</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://seti.net/engineering/threads/threads.php\">Multithreading - The Delphi Way</a></i>.&#160;» <a href=\"/Thread\" title=\"Thread\">Thread</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Delphi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=119042\">Delphi / Winboard</a> by <a href=\"/Tony_van_Roon-Werten\" title=\"Tony van Roon-Werten\">Tony Werten</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 13, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/WinBoard\" title=\"WinBoard\">WinBoard</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=145411\">Delphi version of TSCP</a> by <a href=\"/Steve_Maughan\" title=\"Steve Maughan\">Steve Maughan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 18, 2000</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=158578\">Delphi/Kylix Compiler</a> by <a href=\"/Olaf_Jenkner\" title=\"Olaf Jenkner\">Olaf Jenkner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 14, 2001</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=217882\">Which is the strongest Delphi chess program?</a> by <a href=\"/Andreas_Herrmann\" title=\"Andreas Herrmann\">Andreas Herrmann</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 14, 2002</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=224455\">Delphi and the UCI Protokoll</a> by <a href=\"/Martin_Bauer\" title=\"Martin Bauer\">Martin Bauer</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 18, 2002&#160;» <a href=\"/UCI\" title=\"UCI\">UCI</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=225107\">One more time Delphi and UCI</a> by <a href=\"/Martin_Bauer\" title=\"Martin Bauer\">Martin Bauer</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 21, 2002</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=312449\">Winboard problem (maybe Delphi only )</a> by <a href=\"/Tony_van_Roon-Werten\" title=\"Tony van Roon-Werten\">Tony Werten</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 22, 2003</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=18&amp;t=47359\">Question for Delphi programmers</a> by Ed Seid, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, April 23, 2004</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=388903\">A Delphi - WinBoard problem</a> by <a href=\"/Martin_Giepmans\" title=\"Martin Giepmans\">Martin Giepmans</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 24, 2004</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://coding.derkeiler.com/Archive/Delphi/borland.public.delphi.non-technical/2005-06/msg00820.html\">What can .Net do for me?</a> by <a href=\"/Linda_Scherzer\" title=\"Linda Scherzer\">Linda Scherzer</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.derkeiler.com/about/\">DerKeiler.com</a>, June 3, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=463632\">Ikarus, FastMM4 and Delphi 2005?</a> by <a href=\"/Steve_Maughan\" title=\"Steve Maughan\">Steve Maughan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 22, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/Ikarus\" title=\"Ikarus\">Ikarus</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29562\">Critter: Pascal vs C</a> by <a href=\"/Richard_Vida\" title=\"Richard Vida\">Richard Vida</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 27, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=40414\">for Pascal fans: Critter</a> by <a href=\"/Richard_Vida\" title=\"Richard Vida\">Richard Vida</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 16, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Critter\" title=\"Critter\">Critter</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"